# Verification Loop

- Run this sequence after meaningful code changes:
  - `cargo fmt`
  - `cargo test`
  - `cargo test --test cli_benchmark -- --ignored --nocapture`
  - `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`
  - `cargo build --release`
- This repo uses Rust edition 2024. If the host `cargo` is too old to parse `Cargo.toml`, rerun the same sequence with `cargo +stable ...`.
- Report failures with concrete command output and fix before finalizing.
- Keep machine-readable output on `stdout`; diagnostics belong on `stderr`.

## Example

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
cargo test && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings

# ❌ BAD (claiming success without verification)
echo "looks good, should pass"
```
